'''Connie Chiu''' (born 1969) is the world's first [[fashion model]] with [[albinism]].

Chiu was born in [[British Hong Kong]] to a [[China|Chinese]] family. Like many people with albinism, she has to protect her [[photosensitive]] eyes and skin from the sunlight. As a result, her family moved to [[Sweden]] when she was seven.

Connie Chiu was first introduced to modeling when her sister asked her to become a model at one of her final shows. At age 25, Chiu began modeling for [[fashion photographer]]s such as [[Terry Richardson]], [[Paul Burley]], [[Heidi Niemala]] and [[Morten Smidt]]. Chiu later studied [[journalism]].

Chiu starred in the music video for the single "Stalker" by [[Recoil (band)|Recoil]], the solo project of [[Depeche Mode]] member [[Alan Wilder]].

