{{pp-blp|small=yes}} {{Infobox politician | name =Estefania Cortes-Vargas | honorific-suffix = [[Legislative Assembly of Alberta|MLA]] | smallimage = Estefania Cortes-Vargas 2015.jpg | caption =Cortes-Vargas in 2015 | birth_date ={{Birth based on age as of date|24|2015|4|27}} | birth_place =[[Colombia]] | residence = | office = Member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Alberta]] for [[Strathcona-Sherwood Park]] | predecessor=[[Dave Quest]] | term_start =May 5, 2015 | term_end = | successor = | party = [[Alberta New Democratic Party]] | religion = | occupation = Educational assistant | alma_mater= }} '''Estefania Cortes-Vargas''' (born 1991) is a [[Colombian Canadians|Colombian-born Canadian]] politician who was elected in the [[Alberta general election, 2015]] to the [[Legislative Assembly of Alberta]], representing the [[electoral district]] of [[Strathcona-Sherwood Park]] as a member of the [[Alberta New Democratic Party]].<ref>[http://globalnews.ca/news/1970421/alberta-election-2015-strathcona-sherwood-park-riding/ "Alberta Election 2015: NDP’s Estefania Cortes-Vargas wins Strathcona-Sherwood Park riding"]. [[Global News]], May 5, 2015.</ref> Upon election they became one of the first three out [[LGBT]] people elected to the Alberta legislature, alongside caucus colleagues [[Michael Connolly (Canadian politician)|Michael Connolly]] and [[Ricardo Miranda]].<ref name=sherwood>[http://www.sherwoodparknews.com/2015/04/30/ndp-candidate-supports-education "NDP candidate supports education"]. ''Sherwood Park News'', April 30, 2015.</ref>
Although Cortes-Vargas was represented in media coverage during the election campaign as female and [[lesbian]],<ref name=sherwood /> in December 2015 they formally came out as [[non-binary]] in the legislature during debate on the inclusion of [[transgender]] rights in the provincial human rights code.<ref name=macleans>[http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/for-the-record-an-alberta-mla-on-battling-gender-identity/ "An Alberta MLA on battling gender identity"]. ''[[Maclean's]]'', December 1, 2015.</ref> While the provincial ''[[Hansard]]'' normally reports members' speeches under the gender honorifics "Mr." or "Ms.", Cortes-Vargas is recorded as "Member Cortes-Vargas".<ref name=macleans/>
