{{Infobox person | name = Nicholas Lens | image = N. Lens (2007-Paris).jpg | caption = Nicholas Lens in [[Paris]] in 2007 | birth_date = 1957 | birth_place = [[Ypres]], Belgium | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Composer]] | URL = [http://www.nicholaslens.com www.nicholaslens.com] }}
'''Nicholas Lens''' (born 1957) is a Belgian composer of contemporary music, particularly known for his operas.<ref name="schott-music1">{{cite web |url=http://www.schott-music.com/shop/persons/featured/nicholas-lens/ |title=Nicholas Lens - Profile |publisher=Schott-music.com |date=1957-11-14 |accessdate=2015-05-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131022183656/http://www.schott-music.com/shop/persons/featured/nicholas-lens/ |archivedate=22 October 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name="Lens Nicholas 1957 &#124; Matrix">{{cite web|url=http://www.matrix-new-music.be/componist/lens-nicholas-1957 |title=Lens Nicholas (1957) &#124; Matrix |publisher=Matrix-new-music.be |date=1957-11-14 |accessdate=2015-05-15}}</ref> His work is published by [[Schott Music]] International (Mainz/New York)<ref name="schott-music1"/> and Mute Song <ref>[http://mutesong.com/writers/nicholas-lens/] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140430091155/http://mutesong.com/writers/nicholas-lens/ |date=30 April 2014 }}</ref> (London) and distributed by [[Sony BMG]] International.
Lens lives alternately in [[Brussels]] and [[Venice]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.agendamagazine.be/en/blog/nicholas-lens-aan-de-opera-met-nick-cave |title=Nicholas Lens: aan de opera met Nick Cave &#124; AGENDA magazine blog |publisher=Agendamagazine.be |date= |accessdate=2015-05-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119123938/http://www.agendamagazine.be/en/blog/nicholas-lens-aan-de-opera-met-nick-cave |archivedate=19 January 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
